2%3ESpring%20cleaning%20season%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20over%2C%20but%20it's%20never%20a%20bad%20time%20to%20examine%20your%20bedding%20and%20swap%20out%20the%20stuff%20that's%20worn%20out%20or%20uncomfortable.%20Some%20bedding%20lasts%20longer%20than%20others.%20Rule%20of%20thumb%3A%20the%20less%20time%20it%20spends%20next%20to%20your%20body%2C%20the%20longer%20it%20will%20last.%20Why%3F%20Well%2C%20because%20we're%20humans%2C%20and%20we're%20kinda%20filthy%2C%20even%20when%20we%20shower%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226bf07949-66d3-4cff-900c-276ddbd7ffb2%5C%22%3EYou%20should%20change%20pillowcases%20more%20often%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESheets%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-pillowcase%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epillowcases%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20enjoy%20a%20nice%20long%20life%2C%20depending%20on%20their%20materials%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20use%20they%20get.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20the%20cheaper%20they%20were%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20the%20more%20often%20you'll%20have%20to%20replace%20them.%20On%20average%2C%20they%20should%20last%20you%20three%20to%20five%20years.%20If%20you've%20got%20multiple%20sets%20and%20rotate%20them%20regularly%2C%20you%20can%20hold%20on%20to%20them%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20they're%20pilling%2C%20stained%2C%20or%20threadbare%2C%20they're%20done.%20Your%20tolerance%20may%20vary%2C%20but%20be%20nice%20to%20yourself.%20Buy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-sheets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20best%20quality%3C%2Fa%3E%20you%20can%20and%20replace%20them%20as%20soon%20as%20you%20no%20longer%20sigh%20with%20pleasure%20when%20you%20slip%20into%20them%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233ca6e32-a051-42e9-a131-3ad46222dff4%5C%22%3EPillows%20should%20be%20washed%20often%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20used%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-wash-sheets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewashing%20your%20sheets%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20pillowcases%20weekly%2C%20but%20you%20may%20be%20forgetting%20about%20the%20pillows%20themselves.%20Pillowcases%20will%20protect%20them%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20but%20you%20should%20really%20be%20laundering%20your%20pillows%20every%20six%20months%20or%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20this%20is%20pretty%20easy%3B%20most%20can%20be%20tossed%20in%20the%20washing%20machine.%20But%20read%20the%20care%20instructions%20%E2%80%94%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20mess%20up%20your%20pillows%20or%20your%20washer.%20The%20adage%20that%20you%20get%20what%20you%20pay%20for%20is%20generally%20true.%20If%20you're%20springing%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-down-pillow%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-quality%20feather%20pillows%3C%2Fa%3E%20you%20can%20keep%20them%20for%20decades%2C%20provided%20you're%20cleaning%20and%20fluffing%20them%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20prefer%20polyfill%2C%20cotton%2C%20or%20foam%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20swap%20those%20out%20more%20frequently.%20Replace%20them%20every%20two%20to%20three%20years%2C%20but%20the%20real%20test%20is%20how%20they%20feel.%20Once%20you%20notice%20clumping%20or%20lumpiness%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20go%20shopping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22326c8937-c047-4633-bd8a-9faa11e0cba0%5C%22%3EMattresses%20and%20comforters%20last%20longer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECommon%20wisdom%20is%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-foam-mattress%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emattress%20lasts%20about%2010%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you%20opt%20for%20something%20super%20fancy%20(and%20expensive)%2C%20you%20may%20get%20more%20mileage%20out%20of%20it%2C%20but%20once%20you%20start%20to%20notice%20any%20sagging%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20get%20a%20new%20one.%20Don't%20put%20this%20off%3B%20your%20joints%20and%20back%20may%20never%20forgive%20you.%20Options%20abound%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20materials%2C%20and%20it's%20easier%20than%20ever%20to%20get%20a%20good%20mattress%20for%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComforters%20are%20the%20real%20workhorses%20of%20the%20bed%20linens.%20They%20should%20last%20from%2015%20to%2025%20years%2C%20provided%20you're%20keeping%20yours%20in%20a%20duvet%20cover%20that's%20washed%20regularly.%20Since%20comforters%20are%20lying%20on%20you%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20other%20way%20around%2C%20they%20can%20maintain%20their%20shape%20and%20loft%20for%20ages.%20Wash%20it%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20year%20according%20to%20the%20manufacturer's%20instructions%2C%20and%20store%20it%20in%20a%20dry%2C%20non-musty%20cupboard%20when%20you're%20not%20using%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20the%20real%20deal%3A%20once%20any%20aspect%20of%20your%20bedding%20starts%20to%20feel%20less%20than%20dreamily%20comfortable%2C%20it's%20probably%20time%20to%20replace%20it.%20Americans%20are%20already%20short%20on%20rest.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F642704%2Famericans-sleeping-less-stressed.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20Gallup%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20that%20fewer%20than%20half%20of%20us%20feel%20we're%20getting%20enough%20sleep.%20The%20numbers%20bear%20this%20out%3B%20over%20the%20past%20century%20the%20national%20average%20of%20hours%20we're%20snoozing%20each%20night%20has%20dropped%20precipitously.%20Obviously%2C%20bedding%20isn't%20to%20blame%2C%20but%20why%20not%20create%20the%20coziest%20nest%20possible%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you've%20decided%20to%20replace%20your%20sheets%20or%20pillows%2C%20get%20the%20old%20ones%20out%20of%20the%20house.%20You%20cannot%20save%20them%20%26quot%3Bjust%20in%20case.%26quot%3B%20You%20are%20allowed%20to%20turn%20sheets%20into%20drop%20cloths%20or%20tear%20them%20up%20for%20cleaning%20rags%2C%20but%20once%20they've%20passed%20their%20prime%2C%20get%20rid%20of%20them.%20You%20deserve%20nice%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-replace-pillows-mattress-sheets-from-professional-declutterer-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719479642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66747e17886e840164be8051%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-replace-pillows-mattress-sheets-from-professional-declutterer-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20less%20time%20bedding%20spends%20touching%20your%20body%2C%20the%20longer%20it%20lasts.%20Pillowcases%20should%20be%20replaced%20every%20three%20to%20five%20years%2C%20comforters%20every%2015.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Julia%20Williamson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-replace-pillows-mattress-sheets-from-professional-declutterer-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20doubled%20my%20salary%20by%20becoming%20a%20travel%20nurse.%20You%20can't%20just%20wait%20around%20for%20a%20raise%20%E2%80%94%20you%20need%20to%20take%20bold%20actions.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chan%20was%20working%20for%20below%20the%20average%20hourly%20rate%20for%20nurses%20in%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c35ad40cf2af6e4f5e5fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELouie%20Chan%20is%20a%20nurse%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Louie%20Chan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELouie%20Chan%20started%20travel%20nursing%20after%20working%20for%20two%20years%20in%20a%20lower-wage%20nursing%20position.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETravel%20nursing%20doubled%20her%20salary%20and%20renewed%20her%20passion%20for%20the%20job%2C%20but%20she%20says%20it%20was%20lonely.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChan%20left%20travel%20nursing%20to%20become%20a%20full-time%20nurse%20coordinator%20and%20made%20over%20%24200%2C000%20last%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fgeezelouiseeeee%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELouie%20Chan%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20a%2030-year-old%20nurse%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20went%20to%20college%20in%202012%2C%20I%20couldn't%20decide%20what%20to%20major%20in.%20My%20Filipino%20parents%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20a%20stable%20job%20because%20it%20would%20bring%20freedom.%20This%20was%20important%20to%20them%20because%20we%20didn't%20have%20much%20money%20growing%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20pursue%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fim-a-travel-nurse-make-great-money-live-across-america-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enursing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20career%20path%20common%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffilipinos-make-up-disproportionate-covid-19-nurse-deaths-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFilipinos%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20perfect%20fit%20for%20me.%20When%20I%20graduated%20from%20nursing%20school%20in%202017%2C%20I%20took%20my%20first%20job%20as%20a%20telemetry%20nurse%20in%20southern%20California%2C%20earning%20%2437%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20years%20of%20working%20at%20that%20same%20hospital%2C%20I%20grew%20my%20wages%20to%20%2445%20an%20hour%2C%20which%20was%20below%20the%20average%20hourly%20rate%20for%20nurses%20in%20California.%20We%20didn't%20have%20a%20nursing%20union%20at%20that%20hospital%20to%20ask%20for%20better%20wages%20and%20got%20very%20small%20yearly%20raises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2289566fd1-d898-4b73-b6e4-3ee71a0c42ab%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20travel%20nursing%20in%202020%20to%20earn%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Louie%20Chan%20wearing%20scrubs%2C%20a%20mask%2C%20and%20additional%20PPO.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c631c40cf2af6e4f5fced%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22528%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChan%20at%20work.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Louie%20Chan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20started%2C%20I%20heard%20there%20was%20a%20bigger%20need%20than%20usual%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-nurses-became-frontline-heroes-covid-19-pandemic-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etravel%20nurses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20leap%20of%20faith%2C%20leave%20my%20family%20behind%2C%20and%20move%20to%20Texas%20for%20my%20first%20gig%20as%20a%20travel%20nurse.%20The%20agency%20I%20signed%20up%20to%20work%20for%20placed%20me%20in%20Texas.%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20say%20in%20where%20I%20went%20for%20that%20first%20assignment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20motivated%20to%20sign%20up%20because%20the%20pay%20was%20extraordinary.%20I%20worked%20six%20days%20a%20week%20and%20did%2012-to-14-hour%20shifts.%20While%20this%20was%20more%20than%20my%20usual%20schedule%2C%20I%20was%20making%20almost%20triple%20my%20former%20amount%20%E2%80%94%20I%20went%20from%20earning%20%2445%20an%20hour%20to%20around%20%24121%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20at%20that%20job%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20and%20then%20returned%20to%20California%20to%20rest%20for%20a%20few%20weeks.%20After%20that%2C%20I%20spent%20two%20years%20working%20as%20a%20travel%20nurse%20at%20different%20hospitals.%20I%20doubled%20my%20salary%2C%20grew%20my%20career%2C%20and%20regained%20my%20passion%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e3322f3-685e-447c-b0b2-d089919104e0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20typical%20travel%20nursing%20job%20lasts%2013%20weeks%2C%20and%20the%20rates%20fluctuate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHospitals%20bring%20in%20travel%20nurses%20because%20they're%20short-staffed.%20Most%20travel%20nursing%20opportunities%20are%20for%2013%20weeks%20at%20a%20specific%20location.%20After%20that%2C%20you%20can%20extend%20your%20contract%20for%20another%2013%20weeks%20or%20longer%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20hospital's%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20open%20positions%20through%20travel-nursing%20agencies.%20When%20I%20returned%20from%20working%20in%20Texas%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20Cedars-Sinai%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20Stanford%20Hospital%20in%20Palo%20Alto.%20As%20COVID-19%20got%20worse%2C%20my%20pay%20as%20a%20travel%20nurse%20got%20higher.%20I%20made%20anywhere%20from%20%246%2C000%20to%20%249%2C000%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20I%20worked%20six%20days%20on%20and%20eight%20days%20off.%20I%20liked%20the%20travel%20nursing%20schedule%20because%20it%20improved%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-work-life-balance-advice-boss-lessons-job-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20used%20my%20free%20time%20to%20travel%20around%20the%20cities%20I%20lived%20in%20and%20start%20a%20side%20hustle%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40geezelouiseeeee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtent%20creator%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20travel%20nurses%20live%20away%20from%20home%2C%20we're%20given%20a%20tax-free%20stipend%20that%20covers%20housing%20and%20meals.%20I'd%20usually%20find%20an%20inexpensive%20hotel%20or%20rent%20a%20short-term%20apartment%20near%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2297d0d960-b405-4756-8ac4-98c6602fd82b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20best%20part%20of%20the%20job%20is%20getting%20to%20live%20in%20new%20cities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20travel%20nurse%2C%20you%20must%20be%20a%20fast%20learner%20because%20you%20enter%20a%20new%20hospital%20and%20start%20working%20almost%20immediately.%20It's%20a%20job%20for%20people%20who%20love%20being%20independent%20and%20can%20quickly%20pick%20up%20on%20the%20hospital's%20work%20culture%20and%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20the%20flexibility.%20I'd%20work%20at%20one%20hospital%20for%2013%20weeks%20and%20then%20take%20a%20month%20off%20to%20rest%20or%20travel%20before%20starting%20a%20new%20job%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20travel%20nursing%20jobs%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20I've%20always%20been%20interested%20in%20living%20in%20another%20country%20like%20Japan%20or%20Australia%20and%20would%20consider%20taking%20a%20travel%20nursing%20job%20abroad.%20If%20you're%20a%20nurse%20who%20wants%20a%20change%20of%20scenery%2C%20this%20is%20a%20dream%20opportunity%2C%20but%20there%20are%20some%20downsides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b1eb460c-fbe8-4629-adff-05401463e0a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20can%20be%20quite%20lonely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20working%20in%20a%20new%20place%2C%20you%20might%20not%20have%20the%20time%20to%20get%20to%20know%20people%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaking-friends-older-age-how-make-new-connections-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20friends%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20my%20shifts%20were%20done%2C%20I'd%20usually%20explore%20the%20city%20on%20my%20own%2C%20and%20every%20now%20and%20then%2C%20I'd%20make%20friends%20at%20work%20who%20I'd%20hang%20out%20with%20during%20my%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20other%20nurses%20weren't%20nice%20to%20travel%20nurses%20because%20they%20knew%20we%20were%20making%20more%20money%20than%20them.%20I%20remember%20getting%20the%20worst%20patient%20assignments%20because%20I%20wasn't%20part%20of%20the%20core%20staff.%20There%20were%20also%20times%20when%20a%20group%20of%20nurses%20ordered%20food%20and%20invited%20everyone%20on%20the%20floor%20except%20the%20travel%20nurses.%20I%20didn't%20let%20their%20attitudes%20or%20comments%20bother%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20hospitals%2C%20the%20nurses%20were%20so%20grateful%20to%20have%20help%20because%20they%20were%20overworked%20and%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20number%20of%20patients.%20In%20those%20jobs%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20making%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e098ef8-0710-4679-8ef8-587b19ce109b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELook%20into%20the%20tax%20implications%20of%20the%20job%20before%20deciding%20to%20become%20a%20travel%20nurse%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20get%20into%20travel%20nursing%20and%20think%20they%20can%20give%20up%20their%20apartment%2C%20pack%20a%20suitcase%2C%20and%20live%20on%20the%20road.%20Travel%20nurses%20get%20tax-free%20stipends%20because%20the%20IRS%20assumes%20they're%20duplicating%20their%20expenses%20by%20paying%20for%20housing%20at%20home%20and%20where%20they%20live%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20committing%20to%20being%20a%20travel%20nurse%2C%20speak%20with%20a%20CPA%20or%20tax%20advisor%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20keep%20those%20tax-free%20stipends%20so%20you%20don't%20accidentally%20commit%20tax%20fraud.%20While%20I%20was%20a%20travel%20nurse%2C%20I%20was%20still%20making%20monthly%20payments%20on%20a%20house%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22312d198b-7f45-4b59-8089-aa7c80deed9e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20days%20as%20a%20travel%20nurse%20are%20over%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20now%20a%20full-time%20nurse%20coordinator%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%20and%20enjoy%20working%20at%20my%20current%20hospital.%20I%20don't%20see%20myself%20pursuing%20travel%20nursing%20in%20the%20US%20again%20because%20I%20made%20over%20%24200%2C000%20last%20year%20and%20it's%20a%20healthy%20working%20environment.%20I%20also%20still%20make%20content%20on%20the%20side%20and%20may%20one%20day%20focus%20on%20that.%3C%