andez%2C%2055%2C%20was%20found%20guilty%20of%20federal%20drug%20and%20weapons%20charges%20in%20March.%20He%20was%20convicted%20in%20a%20US%20federal%20court%20on%20three%20counts%2C%20including%20cocaine%20importation%20and%20weapons%20offences.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnProsecutors%20said%20he%20built%20his%20political%20career%20on%20bribes%20from%20traffickers%20and%20protected%20them%20from%20extradition%20and%20prosecution.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EEarly%20involvement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnJuan%20Orlando%20Hernandez's%20involvement%20in%20the%20drug%20trade%20dates%20back%20to%20at%20least%202004%2C%20when%20he%20was%20a%20congressman%20in%20Honduras.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20allegedly%20accepted%20bribes%20from%20drug%20traffickers%20in%20Honduras%2C%20Mexico%20and%20beyond%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20political%20favours%20and%20protection%2C%20stated%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fpr%2Fjuan-orlando-hernandez-former-president-honduras-convicted-manhattan-federal-court%C2%A0%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ERise%20to%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAs%20Hernandez's%20political%20career%20advanced%2C%20so%20did%20his%20involvement%20in%20the%20drug%20trade.%20He%20became%20the%20President%20of%20Honduras%20in%202014%20and%20used%20his%20position%20to%20expand%20his%20drug%20empire.%20He%20allegedly%20worked%20with%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20drug%20traffickers%2C%20including%20the%20Sinaloa%20Cartel%2C%20to%20transport%20tons%20of%20cocaine%20through%20Honduras%20and%20into%20the%20US.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EAbuse%20of%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnJuan%20Orlando%20Hernandez%20presented%20himself%20as%20an%20advocate%20against%20drug%20trafficking%20in%20public%2C%20but%20in%20reality%2C%20he%20colluded%20with%20and%20protected%20the%20interests%20of%20drug%20traffickers%20who%20supported%20him.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnHe%20selectively%20upheld%20extraditions%2C%20allowing%20certain%20drug%20traffickers%20to%20remain%20in%20Honduras%20while%20others%20were%20extradited%20to%20the%20US.%20Hernandez%20also%20used%20Honduran%20institutions%2C%20including%20the%20police%20and%20military%2C%20to%20protect%20his%20drug%20trafficking%20operation%2C%20as%20per%20the%20press%20release.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EViolence%20and%20murder%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAccording%20to%20reports%2C%20Hernandez's%20drug%20empire%20was%20responsible%20for%20more%20than%20130%20murders%2C%20including%20the%20killings%20of%20rival%20traffickers%20and%20those%20who%20threatened%20his%20operation.%20His%20brother%2C%20Juan%20Antonio%20%26quot%3BTony%26quot%3B%20Hernandez%2C%20was%20also%20involved%20in%20the%20drug%20trade%20and%20was%20convicted%20in%20the%20US%20for%20cocaine%20trafficking.%20Countless%20others%20disappeared%20or%20were%20tortured%3B%20their%20fates%20unknown.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ESentence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnHernandez%20was%20convicted%20on%20three%20counts%20of%20importing%20cocaine%20into%20the%20US%20(10%20years%20to%20life%20in%20prison)%2C%20using%20machine%20guns%20and%20destructive%20devices%20in%20the%20drug%20trade%20(additional%2030%20years%20in%20prison)%20and%20conspiring%20to%20use%20and%20carry%20machine%20guns%20and%20destructive%20devices%20in%20the%20drug%20trade%20(up%20to%20life%20in%20prison).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719468720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F2eqisb88_juan-orlando-hernandez_625x300_27_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fjuan-orlando-hernandez-cocaine-worth-10-billion-130-murders-ex-honduran-presidents-drug-empire-5979422%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Juan%20Orlando%20Hernandez%20was%20convicted%20in%20a%20US%20federal%20court%20on%20three%20counts%2C%20inclu