al%20mission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20is%20honored%20to%20be%20entrusted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNASA%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40NASA%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20support%20this%20critical%20mission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F63zFgM5oFn%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F63zFgM5oFn%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20SpaceX%20(%40SpaceX)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSpaceX%2Fstatus%2F1806112279068659802%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJune%2026%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20ISS%20is%20decommissioned%2C%20NASA%20intends%20to%20transition%20into%20smaller%2C%20privately%20owned%20space%20stations%20closer%20to%20the%20Earth's%20surface%2C%20or%20in%20Low%20Earth%20Orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BU.S.%20industry%20is%20developing%20these%20commercial%20destinations%20to%20begin%20operations%20in%20the%20late%202020s%20for%20both%20government%20and%20private-sector%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fhumans-in-space%2Fcommercial-space%2Flow-earth-orbit-economy%2Fcommercial-destinations-in-low-earth-orbit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA's%20website%20states%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ISS%2C%20launched%20in%201998%2C%20is%20a%20925%2C000-pound%20structure%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fimage-article%2Fcomparison-of-size-of-international-space-station%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNASA%2C-Feb%252002%252C%25202020%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520International%2520Space%2520Station%2520measures%2Cend%2520zones%2520(360%2520feet).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeasures%20357%20feet%20end-to-end%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20almost%20the%20length%20of%20a%20football%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20managed%20by%20five%20space%20agencies%20since%20its%20launch%3A%20NASA%2C%20CSA%20(Canadian%20Space%20Agency)%2C%20ESA%20(European%20Space%20Agency)%2C%20JAXA%20(Japan%20Aerospace%20Exploration%20Agency)%2C%20and%20Russia's%20State%20Space%20Corporation%20Roscosmos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20said%20that%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20participating%20countries%20of%20the%20ESA%20have%20remained%20committed%20to%20operating%20the%20ISS%20until%20it%20retires%20in%202030.%20Russia%20has%20committed%20to%20maintaining%20operations%20until%20at%20least%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20structure%20has%20much%20to%20show%20for%20its%20years%20in%20operation%2C%20having%20supported%203%2C300%20experiments%20that%20could%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20on%20Earth%2C%20per%20NASA's%20statement%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20has%20been%20NASA's%20commercial%20partners%20for%20years.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%20two%20American%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fnews-release%2Fnasa-chooses-american-companies-to-transport-u-s-astronauts-to-international-space-station%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%20tapped%20in%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20explore%20commercial%20space%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20and%20NASA%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20made%20outside%20normal%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-nasa-drag-international-space-station-out-of-orbit-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719459866000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660d1c5b1caec1275a6c3e32%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-nasa-drag-international-space-station-ou